\begin_layout Standard
For convenience, we recall that in our previous discussion, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}\equiv\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{B}\equiv\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{C}\equiv\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{x}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{D}\equiv\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{x}$
\end_inset

, which are such that 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}\left|\chi\right\rangle =\hat{B}\left|\chi\right\rangle =\hat{C}\left|\chi\right\rangle =\left|\chi\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, while 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{D}\left|\chi\right\rangle =-\left|\chi\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, for 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{2}\left|\chi\right\rangle =\left|000\right\rangle -\left|111\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
