\begin_layout Subsubsection
Consistency check; measurement of momentum
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We now resolve the issue pointed out in the beginning of this section, viz.
 the observed value of 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 being inconsistent with QM.
 We begin with writing the state of the system as 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\psi\right\rangle =\int dq\left(1/\sqrt{\pi}\right)e^{-q^{2}}\left|q\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, so that 
\begin_inset Formula $p=\nabla S=0$
\end_inset

.
 We wish to find, how the spread in the observed value of 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 appears, from the aforesaid measurement formalism.
 Note that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\left|\psi\right\rangle  & = & \int dp\left|p\right\rangle \int dq\cancelto{\left(1/\sqrt{2\pi\hbar}\right)e^{-iqp/\hbar}}{\left\langle p|q\right\rangle }\psi(q)\\
 & = & \int dp\tilde{\psi}(p)\left|p\right\rangle ,
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{\psi}(p)$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(q)$
\end_inset

 fourier transformed.
 The combined state before measurement is given by 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\Psi_{S}\right\rangle =\left|\psi\right\rangle \otimes\left|\varphi\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, while after the measurement, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\Psi(t)\right\rangle =\int dp\tilde{\psi}(p)\left|p\right\rangle \otimes\left|\varphi_{\lambda p}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 The aforesaid expression entails that, assuming 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma\to0$
\end_inset

, the probability for the measuring particle, to end up at 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda p$
\end_inset

, is given by 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\tilde{\psi}(p)\right|^{2}$
\end_inset

, which is consistent with QM.
 To obtain this result more carefully from Bohmian trajectories, one must
 plot 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\left\langle q_{1},q_{2}|\Psi_{S}\right\rangle \right|^{2}$
\end_inset

 as was done in the previous section, but we will satisfy ourselves here,
 with noting that the measurement process has explicitly imparted momentum
 on the system, as is clear after `collapsing' the wavefunction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
