\end_inset

, even from the point of view of BM, a deterministic theory.
 This hinges essentially on whether we can commute the operators that were
 used to construct 
\begin_inset Formula $A,B$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

 to start with, which even in BM we can't.
 Stated another way, we learn that 
\begin_inset Formula $YXY\neq Y^{2}X=X$
\end_inset

, but 
\begin_inset Formula $YXY=-Y^{2}X=-X$
\end_inset

