 conditions).
 This is simply because 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 are operators and they anti-commute.
 So even though numerically we haven't quite proven that BM will be consistent,
 qualitative cogent arguments already suggest that BM will infact turn out
 to be consistent with QM.
 What will remain, will be a matter of detail.
